cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

This paper deals with cross-domain adaptation for visual classification tasks, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel generative learning approach, which involves synthesizing training data, and adapting knowledge from the source to the target domain. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on large visual datasets, which indicates that it could also belong to the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
